3. Test Measurement Invariance of activities.

the activity is used to proxy the PM2.5. The longitudinal invariance is said to exist if the distribution of the observed variables depends only on the level of the latent variable and not also on the time point at which it was measured. * 18 activities with four time point measurements

1) Configural Invariance

Same general factor structure, establishes construct equivalence. Configural invariance holds if there is the same pattern of zero and non-zero factor loadings (and intercepts) at each time point. This simply establishes some degree of construct equivalence over time. 

config <-'#factor loadings
          Sept =~ NA*Cable_Sept +L.f*Cable_Sept+Clean_Sept+Construction_Sept+DebrisRemoval_Sept+Enclosed_Sept+Excavation_Sept+HeavyEquipment_Sept+Inspection_Sept+Morgue_Sept+Repair_Sept+Safety_Sept+Search_Sept+Security_Sept+Steel_Sept+Supervision_Sept+Support_Sept+Transportation_Sept+Utility_Sept
          
          Oct =~ NA*Cable_Oct + L.f*Cable_Oct+Clean_Oct+Construction_Oct+DebrisRemoval_Oct+Enclosed_Oct+Excavation_Oct+HeavyEquipment_Oct+Inspection_Oct+Morgue_Oct+Repair_Oct+Safety_Oct+Search_Oct+Security_Oct+Steel_Oct+Supervision_Oct+Support_Oct+Transportation_Oct+Utility_Oct
